        "label": "Service User access key ID and API secret",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.m3ter.com/guides/authenticating-with-the-platform/service-authentication",
        "setup": "In the [m3ter Service Authentication guide](https://docs.m3ter.com/guides/authenticating-with-the-platform/service-authentication), sign in to the m3ter Console, go to `Settings` → `Access` → `Service Users`, open a service user, and select `Generate Access Key`. Copy the generated `Access Key ID` and `API Secret` from the popup; the `API Secret` is shown only once. Grant the service user the permissions needed for your API usage.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "bearer_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "OAuth 2.0 bearer token for a Service User",
        "generateUrl": "https://docs.m3ter.com/api/auth/get-token.md",
        "setup": "First generate a Service User `Access Key ID` and `API Secret` via the [Service Authentication guide](https://docs.m3ter.com/guides/authenticating-with-the-platform/service-authentication). Then call `POST https://api.m3ter.com/oauth/token` with HTTP Basic auth using `Access Key ID:API Secret` and form field `grant_type=client_credentials` as shown in the [Get Token API reference](https://docs.m3ter.com/api/auth/get-token.md). Use the returned `access_token` as a Bearer token in subsequent API calls. Tokens are valid for 18,000 seconds.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
